personalInfo.education: University of North Carolina-Pembroke (2012, Sports and Exercise)

tourBios.otherCarHigh: Won eight times in college...Earned 2008 Peach Belt Conference Freshman of the Year...Was the 2012 Beach Belt Conference Player of the Year...Captured three-time All-American honors and was a two-time All-American scholar while also a member of the 2012 Academic All-America team.
tourBios.personal: Worked as a bagel maker for three years...Lists attending his first Duke basketball game at Cameron Indoor Stadium as his biggest thrill...Keeps a memento of his grandfather that hangs on his golf bag...Favorite TV shows are "Elementary," "Jeopardy!" and "SportsCenter."...Favorite course is Chambers Bay and favorite professional team is the New England Patriots...His bucket list includes attending or playing in the Ryder Cup, to one day have a family and "make a significant difference in somebody's life not close to me."

dyn.dynBios: 3-Time All-American, 2012 Academic All-American team member, 8-Time Collegiate winner
dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the PGA TOUR Canada was T59th in 2014 at the Forces and Families Open.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks 17th in Par 3 Birdie or Better Leaders on the PGA TOUR Canada.
